config DONGLE_UNPAIR_HOLD_MS
    int "Button hold duration to unpair (ms)"
    default 5000
    range 1000 30000
    help
      How long the pair button must be held while paired to forget the peer.

config DONGLE_NOLED
    bool "Disable dongle status LED entirely"
    default n
    help
      Forces &led_strip to stay disabled. The WS2812 devicetree node is
      disabled in the overlay and led_status_*() become compile-time
      no-ops, so no SPI traffic is ever generated for the status LED.

config DONGLE_LED_BRIGHTNESS
    int "Status LED brightness percent (0-100)"
    default 7
    range 0 100
    help
      Scales the WS2812 RGB channels for the status LED.

config DONGLE_NO_ACTIVE_EFFECTS
    bool "Suspend status LED bus while paired"
    default n
    select PM_DEVICE
    help
      When enabled and the dongle is paired, the LED is driven dark and
      the WS2812's SPI bus is put into PM suspend (sleep pinctrl state).
      The LED thread keeps running but performs no SPI traffic until
      the dongle becomes unpaired again. Hop flashes, shell-relay
      indicators and the connected/idle colors are all suppressed for
      the duration. Unpaired/armed states are unaffected.

