config DONGLE_LED_NOLINK_FLASH_MS
    int "No-link indicator flash duration (ms)"
    default 300
    range 50 2000
    help
      Dual-purpose status indicator: a one-shot flash of this duration
      fires on every channel hop (speculative or cooperative), and the
      same color is held solid while the dongle is paired but cannot
      reach the peer (rollback dwell, post-validate-fail revert window).
      Flash overrides all other LED states for the duration; solid
      overrides connected/idle but yields to shell relay/pending.

config DONGLE_LED_STACK_SIZE
    int "LED status thread stack size (bytes)"
    default 1024
    range 512 4096

